                "logprobs": [],
                "text": "On that page, the **“Sources”** section explains that:\n\n- When you use the web search tools, you can get **all URLs the model retrieved** by requesting the `sources` field in the tool output (e.g., via `include: [\"web_search_call.action.sources\"]` in the Responses API). ([developers.openai.com](https://developers.openai.com/api/docs/guides/tools-web-search))  \n- **Inline citations** in the model’s text only point to the **most relevant** references actually cited in the answer, whereas **`sources` returns the full list of URLs** the model consulted. The list of sources is often longer than the list of citations. ([developers.openai.com](https://developers.openai.com/api/docs/guides/tools-web-search))  \n- **Real‑time third‑party feeds** (like sports, weather, and finance data) also appear in this list, labeled as `oai-sports`, `oai-weather`, or `oai-finance`. ([developers.openai.com](https://developers.openai.com/api/docs/guides/tools-web-search))  \n- The `sources` field is available for both the **`web_search`** and **`web_search_preview`** tools. ([developers.openai.com](https://developers.openai.com/api/docs/guides/tools-web-search))"
